From: Dmitry Kasatkin <dmitry.kasatkin@intel.com>
Date: Thu, 26 Jan 2012 19:13:20 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] lib/mpi: added comment on divide by 0 case
Git-commit: a6d68ecc56ed182644c81ef6917ce1f5404db7dd
Patch-mainline: v3.3
References: fate#314508
Target: SLE-11 SP3

Comment explains that existing clients do not call this function
with dsize == 0, which means that 1/0 should not happen.

Signed-off-by: Dmitry Kasatkin <dmitry.kasatkin@intel.com>
Reviewed-by: Tetsuo Handa <penguin-kernel@I-love.SAKURA.ne.jp>
Signed-off-by: James Morris <jmorris@namei.org>
Acked-by: Lee, Chun-Yi <jlee@suse.com>
---
 lib/mpi/mpih-div.c |    4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

--- a/lib/mpi/mpih-div.c
+++ b/lib/mpi/mpih-div.c
@@ -217,6 +217,10 @@ mpihelp_divrem(mpi_ptr_t qp, mpi_size_t
 	case 0:
 		/* We are asked to divide by zero, so go ahead and do it!  (To make
 		   the compiler not remove this statement, return the value.)  */
+		/*
+		 * existing clients of this function have been modified
+		 * not to call it with dsize == 0, so this should not happen
+		 */
 		return 1 / dsize;
 
 	case 1:
